  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a gradient-boosted machine-learning surrogate model trained to predict pump-induced hemolysis index for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The ML model replaces the full CFD solve for rapid design-space exploration. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Validation evidence covers nominal operating conditions drawn from the same distribution as training data. No robustness, distribution-shift, noise-injection, or adversarial perturbation testing has been performed.",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
