    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for MRL 2. The gradient-boosted hemolysis surrogate achieves MAPE of 3.7 % and R² of 0.961 on the nominal test set, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all five COU operating points. The six remaining factors are not assessed, which is acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. The credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device.",
